{"lemma": "عِلْجٌ", "slug": "عِلْجٌ", "root": "ع.ل.ج", "root_slug": "ع-ل-ج", "root_link": "/words/roots/ع-ل-ج", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 3}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n30196"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%90%D9%84%D9%92%D8%AC%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "sturdy man", "fa": "مرد قوی", "ur": "مضبوط آدمی", "tr": "sağlam adam", "id": "pria kuat", "bn": "দৃঢ়পদ পুরুষ", "es": "hombre robusto", "fr": "homme robuste", "de": "kräftiger Mann", "ru": "крепкий мужчина", "zh": "强壮男子"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "sturdy man, bulky bloke"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "atheist, kafir", "tags": ["archaic", "slur"], "examples": [{"text": "إِنَّهُ بَلَغَنِي أَنَّ رِجَالاً مِنْكُمْ يَطْلُبُونَ الْعِلْجَ حَتَّى إِذَا أَسْنَدَ فِي الْجَبَلِ وَامْتَنَعَ", "english": "It has reached me that some of your men would seek and chase a non-believer till he retreats to the mountains."}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "wild ass, onager"}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Connected by Jakob Barth to Ge'ez አድግ (ʾädg, “ass”); as a nickname originating in some ancient dialect therewith inviting to draw a parallel with عَلَس (ʕalas, “emmer”) vs. عَدَس (ʕadas, “lentil”).\nThe word was quite obscure until the 2003 invasion of Iraq, when the Iraqi information minister Muhammad Saeed al-Sahhaf aka \"Comical Ali\" started frequently using it to refer to the invading American troops. It was a hassle for translators, and sparked debate in Arabic-language media regarding its meaning and etymology."}, "ipa": ["/ʕild͡ʒ/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n30196", "headword_ar": "عِلْجٌ", "root": "Elj", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A strong,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sturdy, man:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a strong,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sturdy, and thick, big,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "coarse, man:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "any man having a beard;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AZ, L, Msb;) not applied to the beardless: (AZ, Msb:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "any"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "man"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "beast"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that is hardy, strong,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sturdy:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "an ass,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K, TA,) in an absolute sense: (TA:) and, (K,) or as some say, (TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a fat and strong wild ass:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a fat and thick, big,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "coarse, wild ass:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a man,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A, O, L, K,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a big,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bulky, man,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh, Msb,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a strong and big,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bulky, man,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the unbelievers of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eajam", "text_ar": "عَجَم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Persians"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or other"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "foreigners"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], (S, A, Mgh, O, L, Msb, K, TA,) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of others;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L;) so called because of the thickness, bigness, or coarseness, of his make: (O:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a strong and big,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bulky, unbeliever:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L:) or simply"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "an unbeliever;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L, Msb;) thus accord. to some of the Arabs, in an absolute sense: (Msb:) fem. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "p", "text_ar": "ة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (L:) pl. [of pauc.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aEolaAjN", "text_ar": "اَعْلَاجٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and [of mult.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EuluwjN", "text_ar": "عُلُوجٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, Msb, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EilajapN", "text_ar": "عِلَجَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and [quasi-pl. n.] ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maEoluwjaA='u", "text_ar": "مَعْلُوجَا=ءُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, O, K,) like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ma$oyuwxaA='u", "text_ar": "مَشْيُوخَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[q. v.], (TA,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maEoluwjaY", "text_ar": "مَعْلُوجَى", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O, L, CK) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maEolajapN", "text_ar": "مَعْلَجَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Sb, R, TA.) El-Hasan applied the epithet"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EuluwjN", "text_ar": "عُلُوجٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", contemptuously, to certain men who neglected the supererogatory prayers before daybreak, performing only [afterwards] the prescribed prayers. (Mgh.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulaAnN", "text_ar": "فُلَانٌ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eiloju maAlK", "text_ar": "عِلْجُ مَالٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_izaA='u maAlK", "text_ar": "اـِزَا=ءُ مَالٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a one is a manager, tender,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "superintendent,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a good pastor, of cattle,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "camels &c."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (S, O, K.) ―         -b3-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EilojN", "text_ar": "عِلْجٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A cake of bread:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Abu-l- 'Omeythil, TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a cake of bread that is thick"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O, K, TA)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the edges"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the edge."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["Msb", "L", "AZ", "S", "K", "TA", "O", "A", "Mgh", "CK"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}